This project includes an "Autopilot Provider" adapter
(src/autopilot-provider.ts) whose method structure and command
translation semantics are derived from:

    pypilot-autopilot-provider
    Copyright (c) Panaaj
    https://github.com/panaaj/pypilot-autopilot-provider
    Apache License 2.0

The upstream project ships its own socket.io client. In our fork we
re-implemented the same command surface on top of the PypilotClient we
already carry (src/pypilot-client.ts) so that a Signal K server with
both plugins effectively active only ever opens ONE socket to the
pypilot_web process on the TinyPilot. This is a functional benefit for
Pi Zero W hardware; no derivative works of the upstream code itself are
distributed.

For the socket.io protocol layer talking to pypilot_web (watch=, name=value)
we independently confirmed it against the upstream pypilot sources
(https://github.com/pypilot/pypilot) which are LGPL-3.0.
